Title: Efficient Note Taking
Description: As my company starts belatedly revamping our corporate structure a lot of things have been changing, including my personal spiral towards a manager schedule vs a maker schedule lately. One thing I have noticed as I track more and more disparate things is that if I don’t start taking better notes now I’m going to fall behind and drown in forgotten caveats sooner than later. The less effective I am at tracking what I need to do (outside of task based work), or need to know across a breadth of projects, people, and responsibilities, the less effective I am going to be at supporting my team.

Title: SQLite Forum: Caution: clang-11.0.0 miscompiles SQLite
Description:
It appears that the clang-11.0.0 compiler mis-compiles sqlite3.c version 3.32.1.
I have checked in a change to SQLite that appears to work around the
problem.  But there might be other bugs.  Therefore,
use clang-11.0.0 with caution and test your applications carefully!

Title: Those Win9x Crashes on Fast Machines…
Description: It is well known that Win9x variants prior to Windows 98 have a tendency to crash on fast CPUs. The definition of “fast” is of course fuzzy but the problems were known to occur on AMD K6-2 processors running at 350 MHz or faster as early as 1998. This led to some acrimony when Microsoft attempted to charge $35 for the fix. The crashes were intermittent on the 350 MHz parts but harder to avoid with faster clock speeds.
